included.description:
Plan and conduct formative and summative UX research for ATT.com, including interviews, customer collaboration, usability testing, cognitive walkthroughs, surveys, competitive analysis, and secondary research.

Deliverables include study design, data analysis and synthesis of findings, informal and formal readouts to stakeholders, and final reports.

Helped set up a Lean usability testing program to support quicker and more iterative feedback to project teams.
included.title: User Experience Researcher

included.description:
Designed, ran, and analyzed research studies, and prepared reports to drive project development.

Used UX methods to research and design tools focused on improving workflow processes for users (methods include field studies, photo survey, flow analysis, root cause analysis, interviews, personas, experience mapping, prototyping, user testing).

UX Projects:

Created Excel/VBA-based inventory with visual management that significantly upgrades user experience, maximizes space utilization and reduces impact on valuable equipment and samples. 

Developed data acquisition templates in Excel to complement two different user workflows, both of which drastically expedite data capture and analysis, including automatically reordering and analyzing results and providing data visualization in real-time to guide rapid decision-making.
included.title: Principal Research Associate

included.description:
Initiated the idea for bringing frozen custard to the Seattle area, and successfully opened a shop without prior business experience while maintaining a day job in research.

Conducted market research, competitive analysis and product development.

Directed all initial branding and design, including logo, packaging, website, advertising and store.

Hired, trained and helped manage employees.
included.title: Co-Founder / Co-Owner

included.description:
Provided remote freelance UX research support for a cloud-based log management and analytics tool company, including research consultation, capturing and organizing research observations from user sessions, identification of key insights, and reports.

Created a tool to collect and manage customer feedback from multiple channels, including Slack, which enabled the team to more effectively track user issues and bugs during a major beta release.
included.title: UX Researcher

included.description:
Provided volunteer UX support including design consultation and user research (methods include heuristic evaluation, cognitive walkthrough, scenarios, usability testing). 

Directed and conducted usability testing of mobile recipe app. Deliverables included study design, participant guide, data collection sheet, analysis, video highlight reels, and summary report to inform UX strategy.
included.title: UX Researcher

included.summary:
I'm a user advocate, critical observer, and creative problem solver who is passionate about effective and intuitive solutions based on data-driven understanding of user needs.

I can leverage a diverse background in research, art, business, customer experience, product development and continuous improvement methodologiesâall strategic proficiencies for developing successful user-centered products.

I have experience with UX research including usability testing (moderated, desktop and mobile, remote and lab), cognitive walkthroughs, interviews, contextual inquiry, customer feedback, competitive analysis, flow and error analyses, creating and testing low and high-fidelity prototypes.

I am versed in study design, hypothesis testing, and data analysis, and conveying those findings to key stakeholders through written reports and presentations. 

I have a background in art exploring social psychology and nonverbal communication through qualitative research using photography and video.

I have an entrepreneurial drive with experience in small business, Lean Six Sigma Management (Green Belt), Voice of the Customer (VoC), product development and branding, customer experience, visual and service design, and marketing.

I am at ease with Macs and PCs, and fluent in MS Office (Excel power user), JMP (SAS) and Prism.  I also use Illustrator, Photoshop, Tableau, Spotfire, Morae, ScreenFlow, GoToMeeting, Axure, UXPin, Illustrator, Photoshop, ScreenFlow, Ovo, iMovie, Slack, and Google apps (Docs, Sheets, Drive).
